  "market_context": "Market shifted from long-term downtrend to bullish after breaking above a protected low; higher timeframe bias became bullish, so only long setups were considered.",
  "key_observation": "Two unmitigated order blocks existed on the 1H chart; the first was tested but lacked CHoCH confirmation on 5M, while the second triggered multiple long entries after clear CHoCH on lower timeframe.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a change of character on the 1H chart after price broke above a protected low, establishing bullish HTF bias and restricting analysis to long opportunities.",
    "Step 2: Marked two unmitigated order blocks (OBs) on the 1H chart as key trading zones, derived from candles preceding strong impulse moves.",
    "Step 3: When price tapped the first OB, zoomed into the 5M chart and observed no change of character (price broke below OB without reversing above prior swing highs), so no trade was taken.",
    "Step 4: When price later tapped the second OB, zoomed into the 5M chart and confirmed a change of character (reversal above prior swing highs), signaling end of short-term downtrend.",
    "Step 5: Entered first long at the 5M OB formed after CHoCH; as price rose, entered second long at a new 5M OB without closing the first; later added third long at another new OB while keeping prior positions open.",
    "Step 6: Managed risk by using reduced position size per trade and accepting that stop-losses might be hit on some legs; target was the previous HTF swing high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price hit stop-loss of second trade but triggered first; third long was added; overall strategy reached target at previous HTF high — described as profitable but with losing legs.",
  "lessons": "Order blocks require lower-timeframe confirmation (e.g., CHoCH); multiple OB entries in same trend can improve win rate; always trade with reduced risk per leg to survive partial stop-outs.",
